<dl id="n40046a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40046a">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40046a"> 46(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ in exchange / for men. S is / duped</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">This theory of the atonement was formulated by Origen. &ldquo;By his successful temptation the devil acquired a right over men. God offered Christ&apos;s soul for that of men. But the devil was duped, as Christ overcame both him and death&rdquo; (p. 367). <small> &ldquo;DEVIL&rdquo; <a name="EBDV" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBDV"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) VIII 122</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
